definition: to act or serve as a cover or front (see front entry 1 sense 7a) for something or someone
examples: … a new initiative targeting brothels and massage parlors fronting for sex trafficking rings.

definition: to assume a fake or false personality to conceal one's true identity and character
examples: Don't front, don't put something out there that you feel isn't realistic and doesn't portray who you are.
Look, we all know you got your heart broken. Stop fronting and write a love song.

definition: confront
examples: went to the woods because I wished … to front only the essential facts of life

definition: to appear before
examples: daily fronted him in some fresh splendor

definition: to be in front of
to be the leader of (a musical group)
examples: appeared as a soloist and fronted bands

definition: to face toward or have frontage on
to supply a front to
to articulate (a sound) with the tongue farther forward
to move (a word or phrase) to the beginning of a sentence
to play in front of (an opposing player) rather than between the player and the basket
to give (someone) the money, material, etc. needed to do something : advance sense 7
examples: She fronted them a loan to get the start-up going.
